\section{Global-sections evaluation isomorphism (iter-045)}
\label{sec:gammaObj_linearEquiv_top}

Iter-044 landed the algebraic input \lstinline{Module.Finite k (Γ(C.left, ⊤))} from \lstinline{[IsIntegral C.left] [IsProper C.hom]} via Mathlib's \lstinline{finite_appTop_of_universallyClosed}. Iter-045 takes the next building-block step in the producer-instance assembly: lifting Mathlib's natural iso $\Gamma_{\Sheaf}(F) \cong F.\mathtt{obj}.\mathtt{obj}\,(\op\top)$ on a site with terminal $\top$ to a \lstinline{LinearEquiv} (the underlying iso is \emph{categorical} in $\ModuleCat\,k$, hence transports to a $k$-LinearEquiv between the carriers).

Mathlib provides \lstinline{Sheaf.ΓNatIsoSheafSections} (\lstinline{Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/GlobalSections.lean}): on a site $J$ with terminal $T$, the global-sections functor $\mathtt{Sheaf.\Gamma}\,J\,A \cong (\mathtt{sheafSections}\,J\,A).\mathtt{obj}\,(\op T)$. For the topology of opens $\mathtt{Opens.grothendieckTopology}\,X$, the terminal is the top open $\top$ (this is \lstinline{Preorder.isTerminalTop} for any preorder with a top element). Specialising the natural iso to a fixed sheaf $F$ via \lstinline{NatIso.app} and converting the resulting categorical iso in $\ModuleCat\,k$ via \lstinline{Iso.toLinearEquiv} gives the desired $\LinearEquiv$.

Combining with iter-044's \lstinline{module_finite_globalSections_of_isProper} via \lstinline{Module.Finite.equiv} (using the \lstinline{.symm} orientation: source \lstinline{Γ(C.left, ⊤)}, target $(\Sheaf.\Gamma).\mathtt{obj}\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)$) yields $\Module.\mathrm{Finite}\,k$ on the global-sections object as a $\ModuleCat\,k$.

\begin{theorem}\leanok
[Global-sections-to-top LinearEquiv]
  \label{thm:Scheme_SheafGammaObj_linearEquiv_top}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.SheafGammaObj_linearEquiv_top}
  \uses{def:Scheme_toModuleKSheaf}
  Let $k$ be a field, $X$ a topological space, and $F : \Sheaf\,(\opens.\mathtt{grothendieckTopology}\,X)\,(\ModuleCat\,k)$. Then there is a $k$-LinearEquiv
  \[
    (\Sheaf.\Gamma\,(\opens.\mathtt{grothendieckTopology}\,X)\,(\ModuleCat\,k)).\mathtt{obj}\,F \;\equivl{k}\; F.\mathtt{obj}.\mathtt{obj}\,(\op \top).
  \]
\end{theorem}

\begin{proof}
  \leanok
  Apply \lstinline{Sheaf.ΓNatIsoSheafSections} with the terminal data $T := \top$ and $\hT := \mathtt{Preorder.isTerminalTop}\,\_$ to get the natural iso $\mathtt{Sheaf.\Gamma}\,J\,A \cong (\mathtt{sheafSections}\,J\,A).\mathtt{obj}\,(\op\top)$ in the functor category. Take the value at the fixed sheaf $F$ via \lstinline{NatIso.app}, obtaining a categorical iso in $\ModuleCat\,k$ between $(\Sheaf.\Gamma).\mathtt{obj}\,F$ and $((\mathtt{sheafSections}\,J\,A).\mathtt{obj}\,(\op\top)).\mathtt{obj}\,F = F.\mathtt{obj}.\mathtt{obj}\,(\op\top)$. Convert the categorical iso to a $\LinearEquiv\,k$ via \lstinline{Iso.toLinearEquiv}.
\end{proof}

